cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.GR (Computer Graphics): The paper discusses the generation of urban maps for FPS games, which involves creating 3D models of buildings, streets, and other objects. This falls under the domain of computer graphics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a multi-agent evolutionary system and machine learning techniques to generate the urban maps. This involves the use of AI algorithms and techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to train a computational agent to capture the intent of the game designer.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper may involve the use of computer vision techniques to analyze and interpret the game designer's intent, as well as to generate the urban maps.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may involve the development of software tools and frameworks to implement the procedural generation of urban maps in FPS games.
